column5: Hey everyone just booked a camping site its called Hillbilly camping resort it is located HWY 11 south kilworthy, muskoka... Needed something for my little guy as it will be his first camping trip.. Just wanted to know if anyone here has heard about this place and is there any fishing spots around this area. I dont get up north all that much just once a year in February for icefishing on Nippissing. If anyone has any suggestions please let me know  Thanks in advance  www.hillbilly.on.ca  1633 Highway 11 South Kilworthy, Muskoka Ontario P0E 1G0 Canada
Billy might be able to help you out?
Kashe lake is close to it. I think it is right on the kashe river but im not sure if you can fish anywhere or not.

I drive by it fairly often and have never been impressed with what I could see and I know of two families that were going to stay there and after a brief tour said we are out of here and went else where.  vance
